@VaishSiddharth


So the hasMember property of FHIR Observations is not a boolean value. It stores a reference to an observation that is part of this observation group. So this should be a ReferenceParam and treated similarly to how we treat Subject, etc.


The FHIR spec actually wants separate parameters for each value type, so value-concept should map to a TokenAndListParam, value-date to a DateRangeParam, value-quantity to a QuantityAndListParam and value-string to a StringAndListParam.

